<section id="en.genesez.core.description.generatorHierarchy">
	<title>Generator Hierarchy</title>
	<epigraph>
		<para>
			In this section the hierarchy of the generators will be
			described.
		</para>
	</epigraph>
	<figure id="fig:en.genesez.core.description.generatorHierarchy.uml">
		<title>Model-snippet of the generator hierarchy</title>
		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject role="html">
				<imagedata align="center"
					fileref="../../../../images/core/en.genesez.core.generatorHierarchy.png" />
			</imageobject>
			<imageobject role="fo">
				<imagedata align="center"
					fileref="../../../../images/core/en.genesez.core.generatorHierarchy.svg"
					scalefit="1" width="50%" />
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	</figure>
	<para>
		As you can see in
		<xref linkend="fig:en.genesez.core.description.generatorHierarchy.uml" />
		there are three hierarchical levels for the Generator. First
		there is
		the normal
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator">
			<literal>Generator</literal>
		</link>
		, if you use this you must configure nearly everything, but
		you can adjust it to
		your needs. There are only some
		default values,
		besides the ones that
		are set for every component, set:
		<simplelist>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.fileEncoding">
					<literal>fileEncoding</literal>
				</link>
				= "utf-8"
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.prDefaultExcludes">
					<literal>prDefaultExcludes</literal>
				</link>
				= false
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.prExcludes">
					<literal>prExcludes</literal>
				</link>
				= ".svn"
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.singleValuedSlot">
					<literal>singleValuedSlot</literal>
				</link>
				= true
			</member>
		</simplelist>
	</para>
	<para>
		Because in most cases some standard configuration is well enough, we
		implemented a
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.DefaultGenerator">
			<literal>DefaultGenerator</literal>
		</link>
		. There the file and folder deletion
		features are already inserted and
		activated, of course you can
		deactivate this with setting
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.deleteEmptyFolders">
			<literal>deleteEmptyFolders</literal>
		</link>
		and/or
		<link
			linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.deleteOldFiles">
			<literal>deleteOldFiles</literal>
		</link>
		to false in the workflow. Furthermore a default ImportBeautifier is
		set, which should be configured with the properties
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importStrings">
			<literal>importStrings</literal>
		</link>
		or
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importRegex">
			<literal>importRegex</literal>
		</link>
		and
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.fileExtensions">
			<literal>fileExtensions</literal>
		</link>
		or setting
		<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importTakeOver">
			<literal>importTakeOver</literal>
		</link>
		to false (see
		<xref linkend="en.genesez.core.configuration.features.ImportBeautifier" />
		). Also the following properties are set
		by default in the
		DefaultGenerator:
		<simplelist>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.excludePackage">
					<literal>excludePackages</literal>
				</link>
				= ""
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.basePackage">
					<literal>basePackage</literal>
				</link>
				= ""
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.useModelName">
					<literal>useModelNameAsBasePackage</literal>
				</link>
				= false
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.sectionComments">
					<literal>generateSectionComments</literal>
				</link>
				= true
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.accessorsForStereotypes">
					<literal>accessorForStereotypes</literal>
				</link>
				= "entity"
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.accessorStereotype">
					<literal>accessorStereotype</literal>
				</link>
				= "accessor"
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.usePropertyVisibilityForAccessors">
					<literal>usePropertyVisibilityForAccessors</literal>
				</link>
				= false
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.deleteOldFiles">
					<literal>deleteOldFiles</literal>
				</link>
				= true
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.deleteEmptyFolders">
					<literal>deleteEmptyFolders</literal>
				</link>
				= true
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importTakeOver">
					<literal>importTakeOver</literal>
				</link>
				= true
			</member>
		</simplelist>
	</para>
	<para>
		You should not forget to set following properties if you want to use
		this Generator:
		<simplelist>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.template">
					<literal>template</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.typeMappingFile">
					<literal>typeMappingFile</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importStrings">
					<literal>importStrings</literal>
				</link>
				or
				<link linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.importRegex">
					<literal>importRegex</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link
					linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.generator.fileExtensions">
					<literal>fileExtensions</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				- maybe another beautifier as
				<link linkend="en.genesez.core.description.features.PostProcessor">
					<literal>postProcessor</literal>
				</link>
				if you wish.
			</member>
			<member>
				(-
				<literal>newAssociationHandling</literal>
				)
			</member>
			<member>
				(-
				<literal>fieldAccess</literal>
				)
			</member>
		</simplelist>
	</para>
	<para>
		For specific purposes we have
		implemented platform or language
		dependent
		generators. These generators
		are pre-configured and should
		work
		with
		only a slight adjustment to your
		needs. Currently implemented
		specific
		generators are:
		<simplelist>
			<member>
				-
				<link linkend="en.genesez.core.configuration.platforms.JavaGenerator">
					<literal>JavaGenerator</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link linkend="">
					<literal>PHPGenerator</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link linkend="">
					<literal>CSharpGenerator</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
			<member>
				-
				<link linkend="">
					<literal>TYPO3Generator</literal>
				</link>
			</member>
		</simplelist>
	</para>
	<note>
		<para>
			The
			<link
				linkend="en.genesez.platforms.common.workflow.components.generator.outputDir">
				<literal>outputDir</literal>
			</link>
			parameter must be set in every Generator.
		</para>
	</note>
</section>